        // after deleting any number of elements.
        // A fixed point at index j in the resulting array means the value at that index is j.

        // We are looking for the longest subsequence nums[i_0], nums[i_1], ..., nums[i_{k-1}]
        // such that for all j in [0, k-1], nums[i_j] == j.
        // This is a greedy problem. We iterate through the original array and greedily select
        // an element if it matches the required value (the current length of the fixed-point subsequence).

        int fixedPoints = 0;

        // fixedPoints also serves as the target index (j) we are currently trying to satisfy.
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // If nums[i] equals the required index 'fixedPoints', we keep this element.
            // It becomes the next fixed point in our subsequence.
